<inglise> EUROPEAN CENTRAL BANK REGULATION (EC) No 2157/1999 of 23 September 1999 on the powers of the European Central Bank to impose sanctions </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA KESKPANGA M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 2157/1999 Euroopa Keskpanga volituste kohta sanktsioonide rakendamiseks 23. september 1999 </eesti>
<inglise> (ECB/1999/4) </inglise>
<eesti> (EKP/1999/4) </eesti>
<inglise> THE GOVERNING COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN CENTRAL BANK, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA KESKPANGA N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community (hereinafter referred to as the Treaty) and in particular to Article 110(3) thereof, to the Statute of the European System of Central Banks and of the European Central Bank (hereinafter referred to as the Statute) and in particular to Articles 34.3 and 19.1 thereof, and to Council Regulation (EC) No 2532/98 of 23 November 1998 concerning the powers of the European Central Bank to impose sanctions(1) (hereinafter referred to as the Council Regulation) and in particular to Article 6(2) thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut (edaspidi "leping"), eriti selle artikli 110 l&otilde;iget 3, ning Euroopa Keskpankade S&uuml;steemi ja Euroopa Keskpanga p&otilde;hikirja (edaspidi "p&otilde;hikiri"), eriti selle artikli 34 l&otilde;iget 3 ja artikli 19 l&otilde;iget 1, ning n&otilde;ukogu 23. novembri 1998. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 2532/98 Euroopa Keskpanga volituste kohta rakendada sanktsioone (1) (edaspidi "n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rus"), eriti selle artikli 6 l&otilde;iget 2, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) according to Article 34.3 of the Statute, in conjunction with Article 43.1 of the Statute, paragraph 8 of Protocol No 25 on certain provisions relating to the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland and paragraph 2 of Protocol No 26 on certain provisions relating to Denmark, this Regulation shall not confer any rights or impose any obligations on a non-participating Member State; </inglise>
<eesti> 1) vastavalt p&otilde;hikirja artikli 34 l&otilde;ikele 3 ja artikli 43 l&otilde;ikele 1 ning protokolli nr 25 (teatavate Suurbritannia ja P&otilde;hja-Iiri &Uuml;hendkuningriiki k&auml;sitlevate s&auml;tete kohta) punktile 8 ja protokolli nr 26 (teatavate Taanit k&auml;sitlevate s&auml;tete kohta) punktile 2 ei anta k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega &otilde;igusi ega m&auml;&auml;rata kohustusi mitteosalevatele liikmesriikidele; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) the Council Regulation has established the limits and conditions under which the European Central Bank (ECB) is entitled to impose fines or periodic penalty payments on undertakings for failure to comply with obligations under its regulations and decisions; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rusega on kehtestatud piirangud ja tingimused, mille kohaselt Euroopa Keskpangal (EKP) on &otilde;igus m&auml;&auml;rata ettev&otilde;tetele trahve ja karistusmakseid, kui need ei ole t&auml;itnud EKP m&auml;&auml;rustest ja otsustest tulenevaid kohustusi; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Article 6(2) of the Council Regulation provides the ECB with the regulatory power to specify the arrangements whereby sanctions may be imposed in accordance with the Council Regulation; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 6 l&otilde;ikega 2 antakse EKP-le volitused selle korra t&auml;psustamiseks, mille kohaselt v&otilde;ib n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse alusel sanktsioone rakendada; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) other Council or ECB Regulations may provide for specific sanctions in specific fields and may refer to this Regulation for the principles and procedures relating to the imposition of such sanctions; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) teistes n&otilde;ukogu v&otilde;i EKP m&auml;&auml;rustes v&otilde;ib konkreetsetes valdkondades ette n&auml;ha erisanktsioonid ning osutada selliste sanktsioonide rakendamisp&otilde;him&otilde;tetele ja -korrale, mis on s&auml;testatud k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) when carrying out the procedure to determine the applicable sanction, the ECB must ensure the widest possible respect of the rights of defence of third parties, in accordance with the general principles of law and the case law of the Court of Justice of the European Communities on the matter, in particular existing case law concerning the inquiry powers of the European Commission in the field of competition; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) kohaldatavate sanktsioonide kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramisel peab EKP tagama, et kolmandate isikute &otilde;igusi kaitsele j&auml;rgitakse nii palju kui v&otilde;imalik ning koosk&otilde;las &otilde;iguse &uuml;ldp&otilde;him&otilde;tetega ja Euroopa Kohtu pretsedendi&otilde;igusega, eelk&otilde;ige olemasoleva pretsedendi&otilde;igusega, mis k&auml;sitleb Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Komisjoni uurimis&otilde;igusi konkurentsi valdkonnas; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) there are no legal obstacles to the exchange of information within the European System of Central Banks (ESCB) relating to the detection of an infringement of ECB Regulations or Decisions; </inglise>
<eesti> 6) Euroopa Keskpankade S&uuml;steemis (EKPS) toimuval infovahetusel seoses EKP m&auml;&auml;ruste v&otilde;i otsuste rikkumise uurimisega ei ole juriidilisi takistusi; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) the principle of ne bis in idem must be respected as regards the initiation of infringement procedures; </inglise>
<eesti> 7) rikkumise puhul algatatava menetluse k&auml;igus tuleb j&auml;rgida ne bis in idem p&otilde;him&otilde;tet; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) the rules governing the powers of the ECB and the competent national central bank in the framework of the infringement procedure must ensure the effective conduct of a thorough investigation of an alleged infringement, while at the same time providing for a high level of protection of the rights of defence of the undertaking concerned and the confidentiality of the infringement procedure; </inglise>
<eesti> 8) eeskirjadega, mis reguleerivad EKP ja riigi p&auml;deva keskpanga volitusi rikkumise puhul algatatava menetluse k&auml;igus, tuleb tagada v&auml;idetava rikkumise t&otilde;hus ja p&otilde;hjalik uurimine ning n&auml;ha kindlalt ette asjaomase ettev&otilde;tte &otilde;igus kaitsele ja rikkumise puhul algatatava menetluse konfidentsiaalsus; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) assistance by the authorities of the Member States may be required to ensure the effective exercise of the powers of the ECB and of the competent national central bank to carry out the infringement procedure; </inglise>
<eesti> 9) liikmesriikide asutustelt v&otilde;ib paluda abi, et tagada EKP ja riigi p&auml;deva keskpanga volituste t&otilde;hus kasutamine rikkumise puhul algatatavas menetluses; </eesti>
<inglise> (10) the undertaking concerned shall have the right to be heard once the inquiry stage, if any, of the infringement procedure has been completed and once it has received the factual results of the inquiry and the notice of objections; </inglise>
<eesti> 10) p&auml;rast seda, kui rikkumise puhul algatatud menetluse v&otilde;imalik uurimisetapp on l&otilde;ppenud ning asjaomasele ettev&otilde;ttele on esitatud uurimise faktilised tulemused ja vastuv&auml;ited, on tal &otilde;igus anda selgitusi; </eesti>
<inglise> (11) an infringement procedure shall be carried out subject to the principles of confidentiality and of professional secrecy; confidentiality or professional secrecy shall not affect the rights of defence of the undertaking concerned; </inglise>
<eesti> 11) rikkumise puhul algatatava menetluse k&auml;igus j&auml;rgitakse konfidentsiaalsuse ja ametisaladuse p&otilde;him&otilde;tet; konfidentsiaalsus ja ametisaladus ei m&otilde;juta asjaomase ettev&otilde;tte &otilde;igust kaitsele; </eesti>
<inglise> (12) a decision on an infringement may be subject to further review by the Governing Council of the ECB; the procedural conditions under which such further review shall take place must be established; </inglise>
<eesti> 12) EKP n&otilde;ukogu v&otilde;ib rikkumise kohta tehtud otsuse uuesti l&auml;bi vaadata; tuleb kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata sellise l&auml;bivaatamise kord; </eesti>
<inglise> (13) for the purposes of enhancing the transparency and the effectiveness of its powers to impose sanctions, the ECB may decide to publish its final decisions regarding sanctions or any information relating thereto; in view of the specific features of financial markets, publication of a decision to impose a sanction shall be an exceptional measure which shall only be taken by the ECB after due consideration of the circumstances of the specific case, the likely effects of such a decision on the reputation of the undertaking concerned and the legitimate business interests of the latter; such a decision to publish must respect the principle of non-discrimination and guarantee a level playing-field; in this context, consultation with the relevant supervisory authorities prior to taking a decision to publish is desirable; the publication of a decision to impose a sanction shall in any event not disclose any information of a confidential nature; </inglise>
<eesti> 13) EKP v&otilde;ib l&auml;bipaistvuse suurendamiseks ja oma volituste t&otilde;hustamiseks sanktsioonide rakendamisel avaldada oma l&otilde;plikud otsused sanktsioonide kohta v&otilde;i muud nende otsustega seotud informatsiooni; kapitaliturgude erijooni silmas pidades peab sanktsiooni rakendamist k&auml;sitleva otsuse avaldamine olema erandlik meede, mida ainult EKP v&otilde;ib v&otilde;tta p&auml;rast seda, kui ta on kaalunud konkreetseid asjaolusid, sellise otsuse v&otilde;imalikku m&otilde;ju asjaomase ettev&otilde;tte mainele ning nimetatud ettev&otilde;tte &otilde;igustatud &auml;rihuve; sellise avaldamisotsuse puhul tuleb j&auml;rgida mittediskrimineerimise p&otilde;him&otilde;tet ja tagada v&otilde;rdne m&auml;nguruum; eelnevat arvestades on soovitatav enne otsuse tegemist konsulteerida asjaomaste j&auml;relevalveasutustega; sanktsioonide rakendamisotsuse avaldamisel ei tohi mingil juhul avalikustada konfidentsiaalset informatsiooni; </eesti>
<inglise> (14) a decision to impose a pecuniary obligation is to be enforced in accordance with Article 256 of the Treaty; whereas national central banks may be delegated to adopt all measures which are necessary to that end; </inglise>
<eesti> 14) otsus rahalise kohustuse m&auml;&auml;ramise kohta viiakse ellu koosk&otilde;las asutamislepingu artikliga 256; riikide keskpankadele v&otilde;ib anda volitused v&otilde;tta k&otilde;ik sel eesm&auml;rgil vajalikud meetmed; </eesti>
<inglise> (15) for the sake of sound and efficient administration, it appears appropriate to provide for a simplified infringement procedure for the penalisation of minor infringements; </inglise>
<eesti> 15) laitmatu ja t&otilde;husa haldamise huvides on asjakohane ette n&auml;ha lihtsustatud kord karistuste m&auml;&auml;ramisel v&auml;iksemate rikkumiste eest; </eesti>
<inglise> (16) this Regulation shall apply to cases of non-compliance foreseen in Article 7(1) of Council Regulation (EC) No 2531/98 of 23 November 1998 concerning the application of minimum reserves by the European Central Bank(2) (hereinafter referred to as the Council Regulation on minimum reserves) within the limits and conditions set out by the same Article 7(2); the particular features of cases of non-compliance with minimum reserve requirements as laid down in Article 7(1) of the Council Regulation on minimum reserves warrant the adoption of a specific legal regime which provides for an expeditious procedure for the imposition of sanctions while, at the same time, not violating the rights of defence of the undertaking concerned; </inglise>
<eesti> 16) k&auml;esolevat m&auml;&auml;rust kohaldatakse n&otilde;ukogu 23. novembri 1998. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2531/98 (2) (kohustuslike reservide kohaldamise kohta Euroopa Keskpanga poolt) (edaspidi "kohustuslikke reserve k&auml;sitlev n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rus") artikli 7 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud rikkumiste suhtes selle artikli 7 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud piires ja tingimustel; kohustuslikke reserve k&auml;sitleva n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 7 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud kohustuslike reservide n&otilde;ude rikkumiste erijoontest tulenevalt tuleb vastu v&otilde;tta &otilde;iguslik erire&zcaron;iim, millega n&auml;hakse ette sanktsioonide rakendamise kiirmenetlus, mis ei kahjusta asjaomase ettev&otilde;tja &otilde;igusi kaitsele; </eesti>
<inglise> (17) the ECB shall act in accordance with the Council Regulation and this Regulation in exercising the powers laid down in Article 7 of Council Regulation (EC) No 2533/98 of 23 November 1998 concerning the collection of statistical information by the European Central Bank(3), </inglise>
<eesti> 17) statistilise teabe kogumist Euroopa Keskpanga poolt k&auml;sitleva n&otilde;ukogu 23. novembri 1998. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2533/98 (3) artiklis 7 s&auml;testatud volituste kasutamisel tegutseb EKP koosk&otilde;las n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse ja k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Definitions </inglise>
<eesti> M&otilde;isted </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Regulation, the term "competent national central bank" shall mean the national central bank of the Member State in whose jurisdiction the alleged infringement has occurred. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses t&auml;hendab "riigi p&auml;dev keskpank" selle liikmesriigi keskpanka, kelle jurisdiktsiooni all v&auml;idetav rikkumine aset leidis. </eesti>
<inglise> Other terms used shall have the same meaning as defined in Article 1 of the Council Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> Teistel kasutatud m&otilde;istetel on n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse artiklis 1 esitatud t&auml;hendus. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Initiation of an infringement procedure </inglise>
<eesti> Menetluse algatamine rikkumise puhul </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> No more than one infringement procedure shall be initiated against the same undertaking based on the same facts. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;he ettev&otilde;tte vastu algatatakse samadel alustel ainult &uuml;ks rikkumisega seotud menetlus. </eesti>
<inglise> For this purpose, no decision on whether or not to initiate an infringement procedure shall be taken by the Executive Board of the ECB or by the competent national central bank until they have informed and consulted with one another. </inglise>
<eesti> EKP juhatus v&otilde;i riigi p&auml;dev keskpank ei tee rikkumise puhul otsust menetluse algatamise kohta enne, kui nad on teineteist informeerinud ja teineteisega konsulteerinud. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Prior to a decision to initiate an infringement procedure, the ECB and/or the competent national central bank may request from the undertaking concerned any information relating to the alleged infringement. </inglise>
<eesti> Enne otsuse tegemist rikkumise puhul menetluse algatamise kohta v&otilde;ivad EKP ja/v&otilde;i riigi p&auml;dev keskpank k&uuml;sida asjaomaselt ettev&otilde;ttelt v&auml;idetava rikkumise kohta igasugust teavet. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Either the Executive Board of the ECB or the competent national central bank, as the case may be, shall, upon request, be entitled to assist and cooperate with the other in carrying out the infringement procedure, in particular by transmitting any information that may be deemed relevant. </inglise>
<eesti> Rikkumise puhul algatatud menetluses v&otilde;ivad EKP juhatus v&otilde;i riigi p&auml;dev keskpank teineteist taotluse korral aidata ja koost&ouml;&ouml;d teha, eelk&otilde;ige edastades teineteisele asjakohaseks peetavat informatsiooni. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> Unless otherwise agreed between the parties concerned, any communication between the ECB or the competent national central bank, as the case may be, and the undertaking concerned shall be conducted in the official Community language (or in one of the official Community languages) of the Member State in whose jurisdiction the alleged infringement has occurred. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui asjaomased pooled ei ole kokku leppinud teisiti, suhtlevad EKP v&otilde;i riigi p&auml;dev keskpank ning asjaomane ettev&otilde;tja selle liikmesriigi ametlikus keeles (v&otilde;i &uuml;hes &uuml;henduse ametlikus keeles), kelle jurisdiktsiooni all v&auml;idetav rikkumine aset leidis. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Powers of the ECB and the competent national central bank </inglise>
<eesti> EKP ja riigi p&auml;deva keskpanga volitused </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The powers conferred by the Council Regulation upon the ECB and the competent national central bank in carrying out the inquiry shall include, for the purpose of obtaining any information relating to the alleged infringement, the right to search for any items of information and the right to conduct a search without prior notification of the undertaking concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> EKP-le ja riigi p&auml;devale keskpangale n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rusega antud volitused uurimiseks ja v&auml;idetava rikkumisega seotud teabe kogumiseks h&otilde;lmavad &otilde;igust hankida igasugust teavet ja &otilde;igust teha uurimisi asjaomasele ettev&otilde;tjale ette teatamata. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The staff of the ECB or of the competent national central bank, as the case may be, who are authorised, in accordance with their respective internal rules, to search for information on the premises of the undertaking concerned, shall exercise their powers upon the production of formal authorisation in writing issued in accordance with their respective internal rules. </inglise>
<eesti> EKP v&otilde;i riigi p&auml;deva keskpanga t&ouml;&ouml;tajad, kellel on vastavate sise-eeskirjadega lubatud hankida teavet asjaomase ettev&otilde;tja ruumidest, esitavad oma volituste kasutamisel ametliku kirjaliku loa, mis on v&auml;lja antud vastavate sise-eeskirjade kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Any request made to the undertaking concerned on the basis of the powers conferred upon the ECB or the competent national central bank, as the case may be, shall specify the subject matter and purpose of the investigation. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;ikides EKP-le v&otilde;i riigi p&auml;devale keskpangale antud volituste alusel asjaomasele ettev&otilde;tjale tehtud taotlustes tuleb nimetada uurimise sisu ja eesm&auml;rk. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> Assistance by the authorities of the Member States </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriikide ametiasutuste abi </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The assistance of the authorities of the Member States may be requested by the ECB or the competent national central bank, as the case may be, as a precautionary measure. </inglise>
<eesti> EKP v&otilde;i riigi p&auml;dev keskpank v&otilde;ivad ettevaatusabin&otilde;una taotleda liikmesriikide ametiasutuste abi. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> No authority of a Member State can act as a substitute for the ECB or the competent national central bank, as the case may be, in the assessment of the need for the investigations. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;kski liikmesriigi ametiasutus ei saa EKPd v&otilde;i riigi p&auml;devat keskpanka uurimisvajaduste hindamisel asendada. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> Notice of objections </inglise>
<eesti> Vastuv&auml;idete esitamine </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The ECB or the competent national central bank, as the case may be, shall notify the undertaking concerned in writing of the factual results of any inquiry carried out and of the objections raised against the undertaking concerned before any decision is taken on the imposition of a sanction. </inglise>
<eesti> Enne otsuse tegemist sanktsioonide rakendamise kohta teatab EKP v&otilde;i riigi p&auml;dev keskpank asjaomasele ettev&otilde;tjale kirjalikult uurimise faktilistest tulemustest ning asjaomase ettev&otilde;tja vastu esitatavatest v&auml;idetest. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The ECB or the competent national central bank, as the case may be, shall, when giving notice of objections, fix a time limit within which the undertaking concerned may inform in writing the ECB or the competent national central bank, as the case may be, of its views on the objections raised, without prejudice to the possibility to develop these views at an oral hearing, if so requested in its written comments. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastuv&auml;idete esitamisel m&auml;&auml;rab EKP v&otilde;i riigi p&auml;dev keskpank t&auml;htaja, mille jooksul asjaomane ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;ib EKP-le v&otilde;i riigi p&auml;devale keskpangale esitada kirjalikult oma arvamuse tema vastu t&otilde;statatud vastuv&auml;idete kohta, ilma et see piiraks v&otilde;imalust avaldada neid arvamusi asja suulisel arutamisel, kui ettev&otilde;te seda oma kirjalikus teatises taotleb. </eesti>
<inglise> This time limit shall be no less than 30 working days and shall start to run from receipt of the notification referred to in paragraph 1. </inglise>
<eesti> See t&auml;htaeg on v&auml;hemalt 30 t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva alates l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud teatise laekumisest. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Further to the response received from the undertaking concerned, the ECB or the competent national central bank, as the case may be, shall decide whether to carry out further inquiries in order to resolve any outstanding issues. </inglise>
<eesti> EKP v&otilde;i riigi p&auml;dev keskpank otsustab, kas p&auml;rast asjaomaselt ettev&otilde;tjalt saadud vastuseid tuleb teha lisauuringuid v&otilde;imalike lahendamata k&uuml;simuste selgitamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> An additional notice of objections pursuant to paragraph 1 shall be sent to the undertaking concerned only if the result of the further inquiries conducted by the ECB or the competent national central bank, as the case may be, is to take new facts into account against the undertaking concerned or to alter the evidence for the contested infringements. </inglise>
<eesti> Uus teade vastuv&auml;idete kohta saadetakse asjaomasele ettev&otilde;tjale l&otilde;ike 1 alusel ainult juhul, kui EKP v&otilde;i riigi p&auml;deva keskpanga tehtud lisauuringute tulemusel tuleb asjaomase ettev&otilde;tja vastu arvesse v&otilde;tta uusi fakte v&otilde;i muuta vaidlustatud rikkumiste kohta esitatud t&otilde;endeid. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> The ECB shall, in its decision to impose a sanction, deal only with those objections which have been notified in the manner outlined in paragraph 1 and in respect of which the undertaking concerned has been afforded the opportunity to make its views known. </inglise>
